,{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَتْبَعُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":4,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَتْبَعْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَتْبَع","in_corpus":true,"count":31,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَتْبَع","in_corpus":true,"count":17,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَتْبَعانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَتْبَعا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَتْبَعانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَتْبَعا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَتْبَعُونَ","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَتْبَعُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَتْبَعْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَتْبَع","in_corpus":true,"count":23,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَتْبَع","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"تَبِعْنا","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"تَبِعْتُ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":120,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَبِعَ","root":"تبع","pos":"V","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3731","n3732","n3738","n3739"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to follow, to succeed, to come after in a sequence","examples":[{"text":"قَوْلٌ مَعْرُوفٌ وَمَغْفِرَةٌ خَيْرٌ مِنْ صَدَقَةٍ يَتْبَعُهَا أَذًى","english":"A kind word with forgiveness is better than almsgiving followed by injury."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to follow physically, to pursue, to move behind in the same path"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to follow, to adhere to, abide by, or obey; to comply with","examples":[{"text":"فَمَنْ تَبِعَ هُدَايَ فَلَا خَوْفٌ عَلَيْهِمْ وَلَا هُمْ يَحْزَنُونَ","english":"Whosoever follows My guidance, on them shall be no fear, nor shall they grieve."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَبِعَ (tabiʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"follower(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a king in ancient Yemen; the ruler of Himyar and Hadramawt"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Uncertain. Lane claims that it is from the root ت ب ع (t b ʕ), in reference to how when one king died, his successor would follow his policies. The unusual plural pattern suggests a borrowing from Old South Arabian, but the cognate root in those languages likely has the same meaning of \"follow\", and is only attested in theophoric names."},"ipa":["/ta.bi.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3731","headword_ar":"تِبْعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A follower"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women: (Lh, * Az:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a passionate lover, and follower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman, (K,) whithersoever she goes: (TA:) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a man: (Lh:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEN","text_ar":"تُبَّعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sedulous seeker"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women. (K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa tiboEu Dil~apK","text_ar":"هُوَ تِبْعُ ضِلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a follower of women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiboEu Dil~apN","text_ar":"تِبْعُ ضِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in whom is no good, and with whom is no good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Th, you only say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiboEu Dil~apK","text_ar":"تِبْعُ ضِلَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA tiboEu h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا تِبْعُ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is what follows this."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tlw","text_ar":"تلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiyEN","text_ar":"تَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n3732","headword_ar":"تَبَعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3738","headword_ar":"تُبَّعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An appellation of each of the Kings of El-Yemen"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who possessed Himyer and Hadramowt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as some add,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sebà;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) but not otherwise; (K, TA;) and the like of this is said in the 'Eyn: (TA:) so called because they followed one another; whenever one died, another took his place, following him in his course of acting: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAbiEapN","text_ar":"تَبَابِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"added as having the meaning of a rel. n.; [as though it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEiY~N","text_ar":"تُبَّعِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanaAbilapN","text_ar":"حَنَابِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanobaliY~N","text_ar":"حَنْبَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] erroneously written in some of the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ttAbEp","text_ar":"تتابعة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbAbEp","text_ar":"تبابعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Himyer were like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAsirap","text_ar":"اَكَاسِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Persians and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayaASirap","text_ar":"قَيَاصِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Romans. (Lth.) In the Kur xliv. 36, it is said in a trad. to mean a particular king, who was a believer, and whose people were unbelievers. (Zj.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEaAsiyb","text_ar":"يَعَاسِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kings of the bees"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the greatest and most beautiful thereof, whom the other bees follow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAbiyEu","text_ar":"تَبَابِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) in the L,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tataAbiEu","text_ar":"تَتَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAbiEu","text_ar":"تَبَابِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tayor","text_ar":"طَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flying things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"birds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and may therefore, perhaps, be meant to indicate what next precedes]. (S.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shadow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) because it follows the sun; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~uEN","text_ar":"تُبُّعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) A poet says, (S,) namely, Soadà El-Juhaneeyeh, (TA,) or Selmà El-Juhaneeyeh, (marginal note in a copy of the S,) bewailing her brother, As'ad,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaridu AlmiyaAhu HaDiyrapN wanafiyDapF\n                      \n                     \n                        wiroda AlqaTaApi A_i*aA A@somaA^al~a Alt~ub~aEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He comes to the waters when people are dwelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staying, there,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDiyrapN","text_ar":"حَضِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when no one is there, as the"},{"kind":"text","text":"bird called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"katáh comes to water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the shade has become contracted at mid-day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Aboo-Leylà, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the shade of night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., this man comes to the waters in the last part of the night, before any one: though it means also the shade of day-time: (TA:) or, accord. to Aboo-Sa'eed Ed- Dareer, the meaning here is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAn","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this is very probably correct; for the bird above mentioned comes to the waters by night, and seldom by day; and hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adal~u mino qaTaApK","text_ar":"اَدَلُّ مِنْ قَطَاةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiboEN","text_ar":"تِبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY A^aY~u tub~aEK huwa","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى اَىُّ تُبَّعٍ هُوَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know not who of men he is."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEN","text_ar":"تُبَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEN","text_ar":"تَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3739","headword_ar":"تُبُّعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tub~aEN","text_ar":"تُبَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}